window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Three Times Best-Selling Author in New Release Books, Amy Perez MS Psychology </b> <br> <b>Number One Best Seller in Forensic Psychology </b>&nbsp;</p> <p>Books by Amy Perez MS Psychology:&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p><i>Manic Episode Series </i></p> <p><i>Schizophrenic Episode Series </i></p> <p><i>Narcissistic Episode Series </i></p> <p><i>Dark Angel Episode Series </i></p> <p><i>21 Keys </i></p> <p><i>Bipolar Disorder: Thriving, Triggers, Love &amp; Relationships </i></p> <p><i>The Psychology of Love, Finances, and Nutrition</i></p> <p><i>Under Water</i> Episode Series</p> <p>Evelyn was a girl with a mental disorder. Every night, she would have horrific dreams, where she was trapped under water and tried to break free from it. There were many nights that she wanted to call the police or her therapist, but always when the moment came, she hesitated because deep down, she knew that this wasn't real, and there was nothing wrong with her life. She had an amazing family who loved her dearly and protected her fiercely. She had good friends at school who were caring and attentive. The thoughts of calling someone never lasted long, because Evelyn quickly realized that all these people in the dream couldn’t help her.</p> <p>About the Author:&nbsp;</p> <p>Amy Perez has a Master's Degree in General Psychology. She has worked in Miami, Florida, with people living with various mental illnesses. She has spent many hours inside mental health facilities with a first-hand patient perspective. Amy lives in Florida with her family and orange tabby. She enjoys reading, writing, cooking, and spending time in nature.&nbsp;</p> <p>Instagram: avidauthor <br> Twitter: @Psychologyamy <br> Facebook Groups: Mental Health Encouragement, I Love Books, Psychology Facts</p>"; 
